    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix time_server_attach_time_source callback data type issue\n\n### Summary\nThe `time_server_attach_time_source` function in the time management module was incorrectly passing the opaque `time_server_t` pointer as callback data to the time source. This caused a type mismatch in the `time_server_tick_callback` function, which expected a `time_server_private_t` pointer to access the `tick_fd` field.\n\nWhen the time source triggered a tick, the callback would attempt to access memory using the wrong pointer type, potentially leading to undefined behavior or crashes. This issue was particularly evident when running in server mode where time synchronization is critical.\n\nThe fix ensures that the correct private structure pointer is passed as callback data, allowing the tick callback to properly notify the time server thread.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/time_manager/time_server.c`: Cast `time_server_t` to `time_server_private_t` when setting callback data in `time_server_attach_time_source`\n\n"
}